      "content": "Nationalism is a necessary component of social cohesion because it fosters a shared sense of identity and purpose among citizens, which is essential for building strong, unified communities. While traditional forms focused on heritage and shared history can indeed strengthen community bonds, the inclusive model I champion ensures that all citizens—regardless of background—feel represented and empowered to contribute. By setting a standard for what makes a nationalism constructive, I aim to prevent the ideology from becoming a source of division, while still honoring the cultural roots that bind us. Ultimately, this approach allows us to maintain a common national identity while celebrating the diverse heritage that makes our society rich.",
      "source": "target",
